@Remark AmigaGuide database for ARose

@Node Main "ARose Documentation"

@{b}ARose Release 1.4@{ub}

Welcome to a new blankermodule for Garshneblanker3.6.

The original Idea for ARose comes from Afterdark for PC and Mac.
After a few minutes of watching, we desided to do it on good old
AMIGA, too. Since Michael studies technical mathematics
it was no problem for him to identify the functions behind
Rose in AfterDark. Then we have built some controltables and
ARose was born. After some tuning it looks better (in my opinion;-)
then Rose itself. Finally I, Wolfgang, have done all the interfaceparts.


     @{" Installation  " Link "Install"}
     @{" Preferences   " Link "Prefs"}
     @{" History       " Link "History"}


If you have any questions, suggestions or other comments regarding
ARose please send them my way at either of the following addresses:

